info.description:
pyWebSMS is a program which let you send sms through internet without opening
any browser. You can send multiple sms, save your contacts, view the history and
much more...

It's completely modular so you can add or remove providers to send sms. You can
make your own module for your provider if it doesn't exists yet by programming
it in Python in a very simple and capable way.

It's written in Python and GTK so you can run it on every platform that support
them and other external dependencies needed by the providers you use.
info.name: pyWebSMS
info.summary: pyWebSMS is an graphical sms sender which supports many programmable providers.
info.html_description:
pyWebSMS is a program which let you send sms through internet without opening any browser. You can send multiple sms, save your contacts, view the history and much more…

It’s completely modular so you can add or remove providers to send sms. You can make your own module for your provider if it doesn’t exists yet by programming it in Python in a very simple and capable way.

It’s written in Python and GTK so you can run it on every platform that support them and other external dependencies needed by the providers you use.
